        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds `openclaw/plugin-sdk/qa-user-flows`, a shared user-flow catalog/planner with surfaces, capability atoms, optional owner mappings, running-gateway execution metadata, and selected/skipped plan output.\n- Reworks live transport standard scenarios to sit on top of the generic user-flow planner and maps channel cases like canary, mention gating, allowlist block, threads, reactions, restart, and help to user-flow metadata.\n- Adds `qa user-flows run` to QA Lab. `run` compiles selected `qa-lab-flow` user flows into existing QA Suite scenario ids, executes the existing suite runner, and can emit JSON with selected/skipped plan details plus executed scenario ids. `list`/`plan` remain future CLI additions rather than shipped commands in this PR.\n- Gates the public root `qa` command behind `OPENCLAW_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_QA_CLI=1` and removes the duplicate private QA CLI env gate.\n- Makes QA Lab/QA Channel facades and runtime sidecars packaged with OpenClaw so the experimental QA CLI path is not source-checkout-only; QA Matrix remains source-checkout-only.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:check-exports && pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check && pnpm lint:plugins:plugin-sdk-subpaths-exported && node --import tsx scripts/generate-runtime-sidecar-paths-baseline.ts --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/cli.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-user-flows.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime.test.ts src/cli/program/private-qa-cli.test.ts src/cli/program/subcli-descriptors.test.ts src/cli/program/register.subclis.test.ts src/infra/run-node.test.ts src/infra/package-dist-inventory.test.ts src/plugins/bundled-plugin-metadata.test.ts src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts src/plugins/loader.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-lab.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-index.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-package-contract-guardrails.test.ts src/plugins/sdk-alias.test.ts src/plugins/contracts/plugin-sdk-root-alias.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/qa-lab/src/user-flow-cli.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/cli.test.ts src/cli/program/private-qa-cli.ts src/cli/program/private-qa-cli.test.ts src/cli/program/subcli-descriptors.test.ts src/cli/program/register.subclis.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/private-qa-bundled-env.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime.test-helpers.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/qa-runner-runtime.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/entrypoints.ts src/plugins/runtime-sidecar-paths-baseline.ts src/plugins/bundled-plugin-metadata.test.ts src/plugins/bundled-plugin-naming.test.ts src/infra/package-dist-inventory.ts src/infra/package-dist-inventory.test.ts src/plugins/sdk-alias.ts src/plugins/sdk-alias.test.ts src/plugin-sdk/root-alias.cjs --threads=8`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint scripts/release-check.ts scripts/openclaw-npm-release-check.ts scripts/check-openclaw-package-tarball.mjs scripts/openclaw-cross-os-release-checks.ts scripts/lib/bundled-plugin-build-entries.mjs src/infra/package-dist-inventory.ts --threads=8`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: OpenClaw now has a shared user-flow planning contract and a gated QA CLI execution path that can select runnable flows, explain skipped flows, and run selected QA Lab-backed flows through the existing QA Suite runner.\nReal environment tested: Local source checkout in `/tmp/openclaw-user-flows`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: see Verification.\nEvidence after fix: Planner tests pass for optional mappings, requested-flow filtering, live-transport-backed flows, unknown id validation, selected/skipped output, and QA CLI tests prove `qa user-flows run --json` forwards selected user flows to existing QA Suite scenario ids while reporting selected/skipped plan details.\nObserved result after fix: User-flow plans carry running-gateway execution metadata and report selected flows plus explicit skip reasons; executable QA Lab-backed flows run via existing QA Suite command plumbing; QA Lab/QA Channel packaging checks now treat those artifacts as packaged OpenClaw assets.\nWhat was not tested: No live Telegram/Slack/etc. lane was run.\n",
